  - education
  - benchmarking
abstract: >
  MOLEKUL is an open-source, pure-Python implementation of Restricted
  Hartree-Fock (RHF) self-consistent field theory for closed-shell molecules.
  It evaluates one- and two-electron integrals analytically via
  McMurchie-Davidson recursions, solves the Roothaan-Hall equations with
  DIIS acceleration, and includes an MP2 correlation-energy layer.
  Designed for education and reproducible benchmarking.
